  "commentary": "With SPX at 6570.67 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6550 (-8.8B) and max positive gamma at 6600 (+8.2B), dealers are currently in buy-the-dip mode just above the amplifying zone, creating upward pressure toward the 6600 resistance wall. The BREAKOUT regime with -19.7B total GEX means any break above 6600 will force dealers to sell into strength, potentially accelerating moves higher, while a drop back below 6550 triggers amplified selling pressure. Key inflection points are the 6550 buy zone (dealers cover shorts aggressively) and 6600 sell zone (dealers hedge long gamma by selling), with 6580 (+5.3B) acting as intermediate resistance.\n\nBottom line: expect volatile swings between 6550-6600 with potential for explosive moves on any breakout from this range.",
